(
  'Burj Al Arab: Everything You Need to Know Before You Visit',
  'burj-al-arab-everything-you-need-to-know',
  'Everything you need to know before visiting Burj Al Arab — the iconic sail-shaped hotel. Dining, afternoon tea, tours, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518684079-3c830dcef090?w=900&q=80" alt="Burj Al Arab sail-shaped luxury hotel Dubai" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Burj Al Arab: Everything You Need to Know Before You Visit</h2>
<p>Standing on its own man-made island off Jumeirah Beach, Burj Al Arab is Dubai''s most recognisable silhouette — the sail-shaped tower that put the city on the world map in 1999. It remains a private hotel, so access is by reservation only, but the experiences inside are worth planning for.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dubai Airport (DXB)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~20 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Downtown Dubai</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~20 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dubai Marina</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~15 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Mall of the Emirates</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~15 min</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>How to Experience Burj Al Arab</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Experience</th><th style="padding:10px;">From (AED)</th><th style="padding:10px;">What''s Included</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Afternoon Tea</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">595+ per person</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Sky-view restaurant, live harpist</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Guided Inside Tour</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">180–250</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Lobby, atrium, architecture story</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Dinner at Al Muntaha</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">700+ per person</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">200m-high dining, tasting menu</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>Overnight Stay</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;">7,000+ per night</td><td style="padding:10px;">Duplex suite, chauffeur, butler</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<div style="background:#fefce8;border:1px solid #fde047;border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin:16px 0;"><p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Good to Know</p><p style="font-size:14px;">Entry to Burj Al Arab is restricted to hotel guests and those with a confirmed dining, tea, or tour reservation. Bookings should be made well in advance, and a smart dress code applies throughout.</p></div>
<h2>Burj Al Arab at a Glance</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Fact</th><th style="padding:10px;">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Height</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">321m — one of the tallest hotels in the world</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Opened</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">1999</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Rooms</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">202 duplex suites, all with butler service</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Best Photo Spot</td><td style="padding:10px;">Jumeirah Beach Public Beach or Umm Suqeim Park</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Book afternoon tea or dining several weeks ahead, especially for sunset slots</li><li>Smart/elegant dress code — no shorts, flip-flops, or sportswear</li><li>The best free photo of Burj Al Arab is from Jumeirah Beach or Kite Beach at sunset</li><li>Combine your visit with nearby Wild Wadi Waterpark or Jumeirah Mosque</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Burj Al Arab sits on its own island off Jumeirah Road, with a dedicated causeway for guests and reservation holders. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> provides fixed-price, reliable transfers from the airport and all Dubai hotels directly to the hotel entrance. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
  true,
  '2026-07-10 09:00:00+00'
),

