),

(
  'Dubai Desert Safari: A Complete Guide for First-Time Visitors',
  'dubai-desert-safari-complete-guide-first-time-visitors',
  'Everything first-time visitors need to know about a Dubai desert safari — dune bashing, camps, camel rides, pricing, and hotel pickup transport.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544620347-c4fd4a3d5957?w=900&q=80" alt="Dubai desert safari dune bashing red sand dunes" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Dubai Desert Safari: A Complete Guide for First-Time Visitors</h2>
<p>Just 45 minutes from the skyscrapers of Downtown Dubai, the red dunes of the Arabian Desert offer one of the city''s most memorable experiences. A desert safari typically combines dune bashing, cultural activities, and a Bedouin-style camp dinner under the stars.</p>
<h2>Popular Desert Areas &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Desert Area</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time from Dubai</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Lahbab / Al Marmoom (Red Dunes)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~45 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Al Awir</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~40 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;">Fossil Rock (Sharjah border)</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~60 min</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Typical Safari Itinerary</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Time</th><th style="padding:10px;">Activity</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">3:00 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Hotel pickup in a 4x4</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">4:00 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dune bashing (30–45 min)</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">4:45 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Sandboarding &amp; camel photo stop</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">5:30 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Sunset over the dunes</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">6:00 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Arrive at Bedouin camp</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">6:30–9:00 PM</td><td style="padding:10px;">BBQ dinner, henna, shisha, belly dance &amp; tanoura shows</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Pricing Guide</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Package</th><th style="padding:10px;">Price (AED per person)</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Standard Shared Safari</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>120–180</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Premium Shared (better camp)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>200–280</strong></td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Private Vehicle (family/group)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>From 600 per vehicle</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Overnight Desert Camping</td><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>350–500</strong></td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Comfort Level Guide</h2>
<div style="background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:150px;font-size:13px;">Dune Bashing</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#ef4444;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:80%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#dc2626;">Bumpy — not for motion sickness</span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:150px;font-size:13px;">Camel Riding</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#eab308;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:40%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#ca8a04;">Easy, short ride</span></div>
<div><span style="display:inline-block;width:150px;font-size:13px;">Camp Dinner</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#22c55e;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:20%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;">Relaxed, family-friendly</span></div>
</div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Wear comfortable clothing and closed shoes for sandboarding</li><li>Pregnant travellers and those with back issues should skip dune bashing and ask for a direct camp transfer</li><li>Book winter months (Nov–Mar) ahead — safaris sell out on weekends</li><li>Bring a light jacket — desert evenings cool down quickly after sunset</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Most desert safaris include hotel pickup, but for a private, unrushed and comfortable journey to the desert or camp, <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price private transfers from the airport and all Dubai hotels. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
