  '2026-07-11 09:00:00+00'
),

(
  'Hatta Dubai: Travel Guide & Transportation Options',
  'hatta-dubai-travel-guide-transportation-options',
  'Complete travel guide to Hatta, Dubai''s mountain enclave — the Hatta Dam, Heritage Village, mountain biking trails, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546412414-8035e1776c9a?w=900&q=80" alt="Hatta Dam turquoise lake and Hajar Mountains Dubai" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Hatta Dubai: Travel Guide &amp; Transportation Options</h2>
<p>Tucked into the Hajar Mountains around 115 km from central Dubai, Hatta is the emirate''s cool-climate escape — a world away from the coastline of skyscrapers, with a turquoise dam lake, restored heritage village, and some of the best mountain biking trails in the GCC.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dubai Airport (DXB)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~1 hr 40 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Downtown Dubai</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~1 hr 30 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dubai Marina</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~1 hr 45 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Hatta Border (Oman)</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~15 min further</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Top Things to Do in Hatta</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Activity</th><th style="padding:10px;">Cost</th><th style="padding:10px;">Duration</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Hatta Dam Kayaking</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">AED 60–100</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">1 hour</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Hatta Heritage Village</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">45–60 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Hatta Mountain Bike Trails</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free trail, rental ~AED 100/day</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">2–4 hours</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Hatta Wadi Hub</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Varies by activity</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Half day</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>Hatta Pools (Wadi)</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;">Free</td><td style="padding:10px;">1–2 hours</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
<div style="background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:160px;font-size:13px;">Nov – Mar</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#22c55e;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:15%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;">Ideal — Cool Mountain Air</span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:160px;font-size:13px;">Apr – May</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#eab308;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:50%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#ca8a04;">Warm, Still Pleasant Mornings</span></div>
<div><span style="display:inline-block;width:160px;font-size:13px;">Jun – Sep</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#ef4444;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:90%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#dc2626;">Very Hot — Early Morning Only</span></div>
</div>
<h2>Recommended Day Trip Itinerary</h2>
<div style="background:#f0f9ff;border:1px solid #bae6fd;border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin:16px 0;"><p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Full-Day Hatta Loop</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;"><li><strong>8:00 AM</strong> — Depart Dubai (allow ~1.5 hours)</li><li><strong>9:30 AM</strong> — Hatta Heritage Village</li><li><strong>10:30 AM</strong> — Hatta Dam kayaking</li><li><strong>12:30 PM</strong> — Lunch at a local restaurant</li><li><strong>2:00 PM</strong> — Hatta Wadi Hub activities or mountain trail drive</li><li><strong>4:00 PM</strong> — Depart back to Dubai</li></ul></div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Fuel up before leaving Dubai — petrol stations are limited once in the mountains</li><li>Mobile signal can be patchy in some wadi areas — download offline maps</li><li>Bring water, sunscreen, and sturdy shoes for trail walking</li><li>A 4x4 is not required for the main dam and village, but helps for deeper wadi routes</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Hatta is roughly 90 minutes from central Dubai via a well-maintained highway. For a relaxed, driver-led day trip without the fatigue of a long return drive, <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price private transfers and day-trip bookings from Dubai. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
  true,
  '2026-07-11 10:00:00+00'
)
